{"questionId":"25035003","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elsie, a librarian, wants to investigate the length of time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> minutes, that people spent in her library on a particular day.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elsie’s data for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn></math> people who visited the library on that particular day is shown in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a22ae009c52eae231f00243099926ab50be0a3cb.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>26</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25035003","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.1b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of k.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}